		"name": "Travel-Deals",
		"description": "## Travel Deals API\n\nThis collection provides a set of RESTful API endpoints for managing travel deals. It is designed to support core CRUD operations against a local Travel Deals service running at `http://localhost:5000`.\n\n### Endpoints Included\n\n- **Create a Deal** — `POST /deals`  \n  Submit a new travel deal to the system.\n\n- **Get All Deals** — `GET /deals`  \n  Retrieve a complete list of all available travel deals.\n\n- **Get a Single Deal** — `GET /deals/:id`  \n  Fetch the details of a specific travel deal by its unique identifier.\n\n### Usage\n\nUse this collection to develop, test, and validate the Travel Deals API during local development. Ensure the server is running on `http://localhost:5000` before sending requests.",
